text:
A general view north from No. 1 Hanson Place, the Williamsburg Savings Bank Building toward the East River and the Williamsburg Bridge, across Fort Greene Park. The building in the foreground is at the S. E. corner of Dekalb Avenue and Fort Greene Place, and is the Brooklyn Technical High School. The Brooklyn Navy Yard is in the left distance.
May 12, 1939

P. L. Sperr

View v is in the same general direction from the Hotel St. George, across the Fulton Street "E" loop.
title: General view - [Brooklyn - Brooklyn Technical High School.]
